import{_ as n,c as t,o as i,a5 as o,cs as a,ct as r,cu as l,cv as c,c2 as s,cw as d,cx as h,cy as m,cz as u,cA as g,cB as b,cC as p,cD as f,cE as _,cF as v,cG as w,cH as y}from"./chunks/framework.CgTIqH8g.js";const E=JSON.parse('{"title":"Labeling and Referencing Numbered Content in Liii STEM","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"docs/guide-lines.md","filePath":"docs/guide-lines.md","lastUpdated":1761037405000}'),k={name:"docs/guide-lines.md"};function P(T,e,x,C,I,M){return i(),t("div",null,[...e[0]||(e[0]=[o('<h1 id="labeling-and-referencing-numbered-content-in-liii-stem" tabindex="-1">Labeling and Referencing Numbered Content in Liii STEM <a class="header-anchor" href="#labeling-and-referencing-numbered-content-in-liii-stem" aria-label="Permalink to “Labeling and Referencing Numbered Content in Liii STEM”">​</a></h1><p>In Liii STEM, you can insert independent <strong>formulas</strong>, <strong>images</strong>, <strong>tables</strong>, and different levels of <strong>sections</strong> and other environments, and easily achieve <strong>automatic numbering</strong> of the above content, labeling to ensure <strong>automatic updating</strong> of serial numbers, and <strong>convenient referencing</strong> in the following text.</p><p>We have also added the <strong>smart reference (smart-ref)</strong> function to help you automatically identify the type of content you want to reference, achieving referencing of all types of content with one command; the <strong>reference preview (preview-ref)</strong> function allows you to preview the content you referenced in the preceding text at any time.</p><blockquote><p>The numbered environments supported by Liii STEM include: images, tables, ordered lists, sections, subsections, all enunciations, displayed formulas, multi-line formulas.</p></blockquote><h2 id="_1-basic-methods-of-numbering-and-labeling" tabindex="-1">1 Basic Methods of Numbering and Labeling <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-basic-methods-of-numbering-and-labeling" aria-label="Permalink to “1 Basic Methods of Numbering and Labeling”">​</a></h2><h2 id="_1-1-content-insertion" tabindex="-1">1.1 Content Insertion <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-1-content-insertion" aria-label="Permalink to “1.1 Content Insertion”">​</a></h2><p>You can insert the content you need in the box by clicking buttons on the Menu Bar or Mode Toolbar. The following will introduce the above three methods in order.</p><h2 id="method-1-menu-insertion" tabindex="-1">Method 1: Menu Insertion <a class="header-anchor" href="#method-1-menu-insertion" aria-label="Permalink to “Method 1: Menu Insertion”">​</a></h2><p>Click <code>Insert</code> in the Menu Bar, select <code>Section</code> / <code>Table</code> / <code>Image</code> / <code>Formula</code> and click, then input or paste your content in the blue box.</p><p><img src="'+a+'" alt="Insertion Demonstration"></p><h2 id="method-2-mode-toolbar-insertion" tabindex="-1">Method 2: Mode Toolbar Insertion <a class="header-anchor" href="#method-2-mode-toolbar-insertion" aria-label="Permalink to “Method 2: Mode Toolbar Insertion”">​</a></h2><p>You can directly select the environment you want to insert in the Mode Toolbar under <strong>Text Mode</strong>, see the figure below for details.</p><p><img src="'+r+'" alt="Insertion Toolbar"></p><blockquote><p>Note! When inserting <strong>tables</strong> and <strong>images</strong>, please make your selection within the red box in the figure below, do not click other buttons. <img src="'+l+'" alt="Toolbar Expansion"></p></blockquote><h2 id="environment-insertion-effect-display" tabindex="-1">Environment Insertion Effect Display <a class="header-anchor" href="#environment-insertion-effect-display" aria-label="Permalink to “Environment Insertion Effect Display”">​</a></h2><p><img src="'+c+'" alt="Insertion Effect Display"></p><h2 id="_1-2-content-numbering" tabindex="-1">1.2 Content Numbering <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-2-content-numbering" aria-label="Permalink to “1.2 Content Numbering”">​</a></h2><p>Switch to <strong>Math Mode</strong>, click the <code>123</code> style button on the Environment Toolbar to number. Generally, figures, tables, and sections are automatically numbered when inserted; if not automatically numbered, you can click the numbering button to number them yourself.</p><p><img src="'+s+'" alt="Click 123 to Number"></p><h2 id="_1-3-using-label-command-to-label-content" tabindex="-1">1.3 Using <code>label</code> Command to Label Content <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-3-using-label-command-to-label-content" aria-label="Permalink to “1.3 Using label Command to Label Content”">​</a></h2><ul><li>At the content you inserted and numbered, sequentially input <code>\\</code> -&gt; <code>label</code>, then press <code>Enter</code>.</li><li>Input a custom name. It is recommended to use the naming format of &quot;category: name&quot;, such as <em>&quot;Fig:model-arch&quot;</em>.</li><li>A blue identifier composed of diamonds and vertical lines will appear to the right of the labeled numbered content.</li></ul><p><img src="'+d+'" alt="Labeling Image"></p><h2 id="_1-4-viewing-labels-inserted-in-formulas" tabindex="-1">1.4 Viewing Labels Inserted in Formulas <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-4-viewing-labels-inserted-in-formulas" aria-label="Permalink to “1.4 Viewing Labels Inserted in Formulas”">​</a></h2><p>In Liii STEM, when you insert labels in formulas, there are two ways to view the inserted label names:</p><h2 id="through-showing-hidden-content" tabindex="-1">Through Showing Hidden Content <a class="header-anchor" href="#through-showing-hidden-content" aria-label="Permalink to “Through Showing Hidden Content”">​</a></h2><ul><li><p>Move the cursor to the label position at the end of the formula;</p></li><li><p>Click <strong>Focus → Show Hidden Content</strong>;</p></li><li><p>The label will be displayed in the editing area.</p><p><img src="'+h+'" alt="Show Hidden Content 1"></p></li></ul><h2 id="through-label-indication-function" tabindex="-1">Through Label Indication Function <a class="header-anchor" href="#through-label-indication-function" aria-label="Permalink to “Through Label Indication Function”">​</a></h2><ul><li><p>Move the cursor to the label position at the end of the formula;</p></li><li><p>Click <strong>Document → Indicate Labels → Detailed</strong>;</p></li><li><p>The label (such as <code>eq-square</code>) will be displayed in the upper right corner of the formula.</p><p><img src="'+m+'" alt="Show Hidden Content 2"></p></li></ul><h2 id="_2-basic-methods-of-referencing" tabindex="-1">2 Basic Methods of Referencing <a class="header-anchor" href="#_2-basic-methods-of-referencing" aria-label="Permalink to “2 Basic Methods of Referencing”">​</a></h2><p>Liii STEM provides two referencing methods. You can use the <strong>traditional method</strong>, which uses the &quot;reference command&quot; to achieve content referencing; or you can use our <strong>new feature</strong>, &quot;smart reference (smart-ref)&quot;, to complete it more efficiently. For details, see section 2 of this guide.</p><h2 id="_2-1-using-reference-command" tabindex="-1">2.1 Using reference Command <a class="header-anchor" href="#_2-1-using-reference-command" aria-label="Permalink to “2.1 Using reference Command”">​</a></h2><ul><li>At the place where you need to reference, first input the type name of the content you are referencing, such as &quot;table&quot;.</li><li>Continue to sequentially input <code>\\</code> -&gt; <code>ref</code>, then press <code>Enter</code>.</li><li>Input the label name of the content to be referenced.</li></ul><blockquote><p>Note: Please ensure your input <strong>exactly matches</strong> the name you previously customized.</p></blockquote><p><img src="'+u+'" alt="reference Command"><img src="'+g+'" alt="reference Completion Effect"><img src="'+b+'" alt="reference Conversion Explanation"></p><h2 id="_2-2-inserting-non-breaking-space" tabindex="-1">2.2 Inserting Non-breaking Space <a class="header-anchor" href="#_2-2-inserting-non-breaking-space" aria-label="Permalink to “2.2 Inserting Non-breaking Space”">​</a></h2><ul><li>Place the cursor at the position where you want to insert.</li><li>Hold down the keyboard <code>Space</code>, while tapping <code>Tab</code>.</li></ul><blockquote><p>Note: Non-breaking Space, i.e., &quot;non-breaking space&quot;, ensures that the two parts before and after are on the same line and will not be broken by line breaks, improving the standardization of article writing.</p></blockquote><h2 id="_3-using-smart-reference-smart-ref-to-achieve-convenient-referencing" tabindex="-1">3 Using Smart Reference (smart-ref) to Achieve Convenient Referencing <a class="header-anchor" href="#_3-using-smart-reference-smart-ref-to-achieve-convenient-referencing" aria-label="Permalink to “3 Using Smart Reference (smart-ref) to Achieve Convenient Referencing”">​</a></h2><p>Smart reference (smart-ref) can <strong>identify</strong> the type of content you want to reference and automatically <strong>generate</strong> it, without you having to manually type the type name and non-breaking space.</p><h2 id="_3-1-enabling-smart-ref" tabindex="-1">3.1 Enabling smart-ref <a class="header-anchor" href="#_3-1-enabling-smart-ref" aria-label="Permalink to “3.1 Enabling smart-ref”">​</a></h2><ul><li>Under <strong>Text Mode</strong>, click the <code>⊕</code> button in the Focus Toolbar.</li><li>In the <code>Utility</code> category, check <code>smart-ref</code>.</li></ul><p><img src="'+p+'" alt="Checking smart-ref"></p><h2 id="_3-2-achieving-quick-referencing" tabindex="-1">3.2 Achieving Quick Referencing <a class="header-anchor" href="#_3-2-achieving-quick-referencing" aria-label="Permalink to “3.2 Achieving Quick Referencing”">​</a></h2><ul><li>Sequentially input <code>\\</code> -&gt; <code>smart-ref</code>, click <code>Enter</code>.</li><li>Input the label name of the content to be referenced, click <code>Enter</code>.</li></ul><p><img src="'+f+'" alt="Inputting smart-ref and Reference Name"><img src="'+_+'" alt="smart-ref Completion Effect"></p><blockquote><p>Note: If you need to disable this plugin, you can click the plugin name in the Focus Toolbar under this text mode and select <code>Cancel Package</code>. The preview-ref plugin below can also be canceled in the same way.</p></blockquote><h2 id="_4-using-preview-plugin-preview-ref-to-achieve-reference-preview" tabindex="-1">4 Using Preview Plugin (preview-ref) to Achieve Reference Preview <a class="header-anchor" href="#_4-using-preview-plugin-preview-ref-to-achieve-reference-preview" aria-label="Permalink to “4 Using Preview Plugin (preview-ref) to Achieve Reference Preview”">​</a></h2><h2 id="_4-1-enabling-preview-ref" tabindex="-1">4.1 Enabling preview-ref <a class="header-anchor" href="#_4-1-enabling-preview-ref" aria-label="Permalink to “4.1 Enabling preview-ref”">​</a></h2><ul><li>Under <strong>Text Mode</strong>, click the <code>⊕</code> button in the Focus Toolbar.</li><li>In the <code>Utility</code> category, check <code>preview-ref</code>.</li></ul><p><img src="'+v+'" alt="Checking preview-ref"></p><h2 id="_4-2-real-time-preview" tabindex="-1">4.2 Real-time Preview <a class="header-anchor" href="#_4-2-real-time-preview" aria-label="Permalink to “4.2 Real-time Preview”">​</a></h2><p>Hover the mouse over the reference number, and you can preview the labeled or referenced content.</p><p><img src="'+w+'" alt="Previewing Formula"><img src="'+y+'" alt="Previewing Image"></p>',53)])])}const S=n(k,[["render",P]]);export{E as __pageData,S as default};
